Label: source
Description: A related resource from which the described resource is derived.

Label: contributor
Description: An entity responsible for making contributions to the resource.

Label: date created
Description: Date of creation of the resource.

Label: creator
Description: An entity responsible for making the resource.

Label: description
Description: An account of the resource.

Label: date modified
Description: Date on which the resource was changed.

Label: publisher
Description: An entity responsible for making the resource available.

Label: title
Description: A name given to the resource.

Label: connected to
Description: Indicates a topological connection or spatial contact between two features.

Label: spatially related to
Description: A general topological connection or spatial contact relationship between features.

Label: Administrative Region
Description: Administrative regions as defined by the Global Administrative Area Database (GADM).

Label: Administrative Region Level 0
Description: GADM level 0 administrative regions which represent countries.

Label: Administrative Region Level 1
Description: GADM level 1 administrative regions which are the highest level of division of a country, such as US states, Canadian provinces, or French departments.

Label: Administrative Region Level 2
Description: GADM level 2 administrative regions which further subdivide states, provinces, or departments. Examples include counties in the US.

Label: Administrative Region Level 3
Description: GADM level 3 administrative regions. In the US, these are subdivisions of counties, formally known as county subdivisions, such as minor civil divisions (e.g. towns or townships) or census county divisions.

Label: Administrative Region Level 4
Description: GADM level 4 administrative regions.

Label: Administrative Region Level 5
Description: GADM level 5 administrative regions.

Label: Administrative Region Level 6
Description: GADM level 6 administrative regions.

Label: Cell
Description: A spatial cell used for discretizing geographic space into regular units.

Label: Place
Description: A named geographic location with cultural or social significance.

Label: Point of Interest
Description: A specific location that someone may find useful or interesting.

Label: Region
Description: A spatial region that represents a bounded area of space.

Label: Road Segment
Description: A linear feature representing a segment of a road network.

Label: S2 Cell
Description: A cell from the S2 discrete global grid system, which hierarchically subdivides the sphere.

Label: S2 Cell Level 0
Description: An S2 cell at zoom level 0, representing one of 6 root cells covering the entire sphere.

Label: S2 Cell Level 1
Description: An S2 cell at zoom level 1, representing approximately 85 million km² at the equator.

Label: S2 Cell Level 10
Description: An S2 cell at zoom level 10, representing approximately 327 km² at the equator.

Label: S2 Cell Level 11
Description: An S2 cell at zoom level 11, representing approximately 81.7 km² at the equator.

Label: S2 Cell Level 12
Description: An S2 cell at zoom level 12, representing approximately 20.4 km² at the equator.

Label: S2 Cell Level 13
Description: An S2 cell at zoom level 13, representing approximately 1.27 km² at the equator.

Label: S2 Cell Level 14
Description: An S2 cell at zoom level 14, representing approximately 1.27 km² at the equator.

Label: S2 Cell Level 15
Description: An S2 cell at zoom level 15, representing approximately 318,000 m² at the equator.

Label: S2 Cell Level 2
Description: An S2 cell at zoom level 2, representing approximately 21 million km² at the equator.

Label: S2 Cell Level 3
Description: An S2 cell at zoom level 3, representing approximately 5.3 million km² at the equator.

Label: S2 Cell Level 4
Description: An S2 cell at zoom level 4, representing approximately 1.3 million km² at the equator.

Label: S2 Cell Level 5
Description: An S2 cell at zoom level 5, representing approximately 332,000 km² at the equator.

Label: S2 Cell Level 6
Description: An S2 cell at zoom level 6, representing approximately 83,000 km² at the equator.

Label: S2 Cell Level 7
Description: An S2 cell at zoom level 7, representing approximately 20,800 km² at the equator.

Label: S2 Cell Level 8
Description: An S2 cell at zoom level 8, representing approximately 5,200 km² at the equator.

Label: S2 Cell Level 9
Description: An S2 cell at zoom level 9, representing approximately 1,300 km² at the equator.

Label: Statistical Area
Description: A geographic area defined for statistical data collection and reporting purposes.

Label: ZIP Code Area
Description: A geographic area defined by a postal ZIP code boundary.

Label: administrative part of
Description: Indicates that one administrative region is a part of another administrative region in the hierarchy.

Label: as Well-Known Text
Description: Provides the WKT (Well-Known Text) serialization of a geometry.

Label: cell identifier
Description: The unique identifier for a spatial cell in a discrete global grid system.

Label: has default geometry
Description: Links a feature to its primary or default geometric representation.

Label: has end time
Description: The ending time of a temporal feature or event.

Label: has FIPS code
Description: Relates a geographic feature to its Federal Information Processing Standards (FIPS) code identifier.

Label: has geometry
Description: Links a spatial feature to one of its geometric representations.

Label: has start time
Description: The beginning time of a temporal feature or event.

Label: has temporal extent
Description: Links a feature to its temporal extent or time period.

Label: spatially contains
Description: Indicates that one geographic feature spatially contains another (DE-9IM pattern T*****FF*).

Label: spatially crosses
Description: Indicates that two geographic features cross each other (DE-9IM pattern T*T****** for line/area).

Label: spatially disjoint
Description: Indicates that two geographic features have no points in common (DE-9IM pattern FF*FF****).

Label: spatially equals
Description: Indicates that two geographic features are spatially equal (DE-9IM pattern TFFFTFFFT).

Label: spatially intersects
Description: Indicates that two geographic features have at least one point in common (opposite of disjoint).

Label: spatially overlaps
Description: Indicates that two geographic features partially overlap (DE-9IM pattern T*T***T** for areas).

Label: spatially touches
Description: Indicates that two geographic features touch at their boundaries but do not overlap (DE-9IM pattern FT******* or F**T***** or F***T****).

Label: spatially within
Description: Indicates that one geographic feature is spatially within another (DE-9IM pattern T*F**F***).

Label: spatial relation
Description: A general spatial relationship between two geographic features.

Label: Feature
Description: A discrete spatial phenomenon representing an abstraction of a real-world entity. From GeoSPARQL specification.

Label: Geometry
Description: A coherent set of direct positions in space representing the shape, size, and location of a geographic feature. From GeoSPARQL specification.

Label: Spatial Object
Description: Anything spatial (e.g., having spatial extent, position). From GeoSPARQL specification.

Label: as WKT
Description: The Well-Known Text (WKT) serialization of a geometry.

Label: default geometry
Description: The default geometric representation to use for a feature when multiple geometries are available.

Label: has geometry
Description: Links a feature to its geometric representation.

Label: has metric area
Description: The area of a spatial object in square meters.
